Task:
0) where folder currently I am in my Linux box : pwd
1) Create a folder: identify command: mkdir <directoryname> : mkdir amit
2) go inside the folder: identify command: cd amit
3) create a empty file: indenfify command:touch <filename> 
4) Read the file: indentify: cat <filename>

To modify or create a new file, we can use editors:

vi,vim,nano

vi: equivalent notepad is doing

Compiler is software which convert the high level code to the machine lang.

-------------------
Shell: we need to mention the complier,
In the scripting file, we present the compier/interpreter by a symbol which is call she-bang
A shebang (#!) is a special two-character sequence at the very beginning of a script file in Unix-like operating systems, telling the kernel which interpreter (like bash, python3)

#!/bin/bash (bash interpreter)
#!/usr/bin/python (python interpreter)
#!/usr/bin/perl (perl interpreter)

Java case-->javaource code-->compile it to java byte code-->interpreter-->machine lagnguage
