Exercise 1: Create Your First User (10 minutes)
Difficulty: EASY
Task: Create a new user named "developer" with a home directory and set a password.
Step 1: Create the user
sudo adduser developer
When prompted:
Enter     password: DevPass123! 
Re-enter     password for confirmation 
Press     Enter to skip optional fields (Full Name, Room Number, etc.) 
Type     'Y' to confirm

Step 2: Verify user creation
# Check if user exists
id developer
 
# Check home directory was created
sudo ls -la /home/developer
 
# View user entry in passwd file
sudo grep developer /etc/passwd

Exercise2

#switch user (su)
su developer
#it will prompt for the password
sudo apt update
#user is not in the  sudoers file

