ssh authentication
AWS-->

Linux based ec2 instance-->keypair (private key)-->public key ec2 instance

some got the access on my system.

Can they access my ec2 instance:

username/password

ssh based--> -->public

private key + passp
--------------------
aws session: key -pair based authentication

How it works?

bank lockers:

two set of keys: one key with owner + second key with bank manager

first they ask to put your key+manager will put his key-->locker will open

Owner-->private key-------------->aws (public key)

send message by using private key encrypton-->(hello)encrypted--->right public key(hello) AUthenticated each other

access denied public key

Private: it will be always owner, you will never share it

Public means: we will send to remote server for authentication (Share)

using ssh protocol hand shake (public mean this something you can share it)

ssh: Secure shell

